cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically with depth and motion estimation from monocular videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a differentiable forward rigid projection module, which is related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) the second likely category. The paper also introduces an auto-annotation scheme, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third likely category. The paper also proposes a mini-batch re-arrangement scheme, which is related to optimization and algorithms, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the fourth likely category. Lastly, the paper deals with instance-wise photometric and geometric consistency loss, which is related to graphics and visualization, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) the fifth likely category.
